  "rationale": "<p>Simplify each radical: <sup>7</sup>&radic;(2<sup>7</sup><i>x</i><sup>21</sup>) = 2<i>x</i>&sup3;, and <sup>9</sup>&radic;(3<sup>9</sup><i>x</i>) = 3<i>x</i><sup>1/9</sup>. Multiplying: 5 &middot; 2<i>x</i>&sup3; &middot; 3<i>x</i><sup>1/9</sup> = 30<i>x</i><sup>3 + 1/9</sup> = 30<i>x</i><sup>28/9</sup>. So <i>a</i> = 30 and <i>b</i> = 28/9. Their sum is 30 + 28/9 = 298/9.</p>",
